Captain Tunji Shelle (rtd), a former state chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) on Sunday said his still holds Chief Olabode George, a former Deputy National Chairman of the party in high esteem despite their disagreement on the management of the party’s affairs in Lagos state. Speaking in an interview with DAILY INDEPENDENT, Shelle who described George as a ‘compassionate and good man’, said even though his disagreement with the Atona Oodua is based on principles, he is confident that the issue between them will soon be resolved as they move towards winning Lagos state for the PDP in the 2023 elections. He said “It is true that l am presently not on the same page with Chief Bode George on the management of the affairs of PDP in Lagos but this has not diminished my respect and love for him. I still hold him in high esteem for his compassion and good deeds”. 2023: Nigeria Can’t Afford Another Setback With Tinubu As… Sanwo-Olu Does Not Deserve Second Term – Shelle “My position is based on principles and l believe that the whole issue will be resolved as we journey towards winning Lagos for PDP together during the next election”. On what the PDP can do to win Lagos state which has been elusive since 1999, Shelle said “We just need to work together as a team and strategise accordingly to ensure that APC does not manipulate and compromise the election results. The tide is very much in our favour”.